  "body": "Hi,\n\nwe have a rather large spring application that can take up to 30/40 seconds to start.\nit is a spring application so its boot is very cpu intensive.\nWe deploy this app in kubernetes (OpenShift actually).\nWhat we notice under load is that if a scale up event is triggered due to load,  sometime almost immediately another scale up event is alsotriggered.\nWe aren't sure about the reason but we think that because the application start is so CPU intensive it triggers another scale event. Sometime this causes a chain reaction that makes the application scale up to the maximum number of instances that we have configured in the HPA.\nWe believe that a possible reason for that is this behavior is that cpu consumption is considered even before the pod is in ready state (based on the readiness probe).\n\nThanks\nRaffaele\n",
